      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is no standard \"safe\" dose of pseudoephedrine I can prescribe to you, as no medication should be self-administered without your doctor's explicit approval due to pregnancy risks. Taking it without knowing your specific medical history and magnesium levels puts your baby at risk of reduced blood flow or other complications. Please consider asking your doctor to extend an existing appointment online or contacting pharmacy benefits to get an immediate referral to a available telehealth provider for safe, personalized advice right now.",
